Description: A Potion of Transmutation can be used to give a player a new role from the faction they belong to. It will not affect Night Immune roles.

A Hvísla Rune allows you to talk to a player the following night. The other player will see all the messages you send at night but will not know who is sending them. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.
A Disruption Orb will roleblock anyone visiting you that is not Night Immune. Unfortunately it will also roleblock you at the same time
Steel Armour will protect you from one night kill.
If you are killed at night whilst in the possession of an Ankh of Reincarnation, you will be revived a day later
A Potion of Cleansing can be used to remove all negative effects applied to a player, like Poison
The Ring of Tenacity prevents its bearer from being Roleblocked
A Wolf Pelt will protect you from one night kill, but it will make you appear as a Werewolf to the Seer

The Sanguine Horn is an ancient werewolf relic, it is said to be covered in the blood of Fenrir, the wolf god. It can be sounded once per game, and will trigger a Blood Moon that will afflict approximately 25% of the village with Lycanthropy.

Bracers such as this were gifted by the wolf gods centuries ago to the mortal archers that fought on their side as reward and insurance for their service. It is imbued with magic that ensures should any wolf ever cause harm to its wearer, the wearer would be given the strength of the wolf themselves.

A Hvísla Rune allows you to talk to a player the following night. The other player will see all the messages you send at night but will not know who is sending them. Holding it will make you appear as a Witch Craft user to intel checks. After use, a Rune must recharge and can be used again by you three nights later. If you pass the Rune to a different player they will be able to use it immediately.

On the drunk idea: it was born from me wanting to put a bunch of TRs in the game but also having a partially unknown setup which would be revealed slowly. However, the TRs seemed to be a bit too strong when I thought about it so kept with the open setup but slow reveal of drunks.  Drunks: The OW could only kill ONE drunk on N1. So I could keep some important roles in play since they don’t visit. (Didn’t expect the OW to get caught so quickly, the fuck was that recruit :P) I like the idea of using them as part of trying to figure out what fits – masons? Seer? To have clues go throughout the game. Like the horn being with wolves, when it’s blown, you think BMC are in and probably a seer since one wasn’t in the original setup so it gives both village and evils a chance to figure out what they think fits. I like the freedom it gives to evils to claim outside the setup since it isn’t all known but have to figure out what they think would fit as a sober role.  I also used them to look like familiars to help the vampire hide a bit more so I had a GD, a cult follower (stalker) and a militia in the sober plan. I had a priority for the roles that needed to sober vs the ones that died.  I did give both “intended seers” whisper runes but unfortunately Winnie the Pooh hated Chipmunks so had to change the player for the real seer. I also had an issue with the final drunk sober since I hadn’t accounted for a sober timing after a revive, I waited until I think the day after, so he sobered at the same “time” Night time change so he didn’t get the dig as the GD was suppose to.  They had specific triggers: Gravedigger	D3 Agitator	D3 Seer	N2 Militia	D2 Beholder	N3 BMC Stalker	D2 BMC Seer	N2  So the morning of D2 a BMC stalker and a militia spawn, two fam roles. Then at the end of D2 you get the seer and BMC seer so they both have a N2 check. Then on the second morning you got another fam role, GD and an agitator, that since items had already revealed might be suspected as an item. Then finally the beholder at the end of D3 if they were still alive.  I considered masons because WHO DOESN’T LOVE A GOOD FACTION WAR. But didn’t think village with wolves and vamp would be able to deal with a faction war as I like them so decided to see if BMC/ Vamp decided to try it :D I also think it wouldn’t be fair to have another group confirming villagers.
ALSO

However it apparently hasn’t been decided what happens when a bracer is on a familiar when a wolf attacks. It was a very slow-moving train crash when the BMC passed it to Donald on the same night he got famed. Anyway, that night Donald was transmuted into a vampire by the vamps transmute potion, then turned into a wolf. I decided based on the item that the kill would have been protected (protects from any harm from wolves) but that the item would still return to the wolves and fam returns to fam.
